{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idab02475c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s7842"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7842"},"text":"§ 7842.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Settlement of accounts of line officers","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Comptroller General shall settle the account of a line officer of the Army for pay due the officer even if the officer cannot account for property entrusted to the officer or cannot make a monthly report or return, when the Comptroller General is satisfied that the inability to account for property or make a report or return was the result of the officer having been a prisoner, or of an accident or casualty of war.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idab02475d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/258/s2/b/10/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–258, § 2(b)(10)(B)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1057"},"text":"96 Stat. 1057","children":[],"tail":", § 4842; renumbered § 7842, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/232/dA/tVIII/s808/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–232, div. A, title VIII, § 808(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/1839"},"text":"132 Stat. 1839","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idab02475e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idab02475f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idab024760-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db